properties.Name: MasterContractBenefitSchedule
properties.Description:
The schedule by which the amount and type of benefits provided by the group life plan to members is determined.

Most employers will establish benefit schedules according to earnings, employment position or flat benefit.

Columns.Name: MasterContractId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Master Contract.

Columns.Name: BenefitComponentId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Benefit Component.

Columns.Name: InsuranceAmount
Columns.Description: The amount of insurance provided under the associated Benefit Components.

Columns.Name: InsurancePercentageOfSalary
Columns.Description: The amount of insurance as a percentage of annual salary provided under the associated Benefit Components.
